  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): `0.3.4`\r\n* OS: win\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): `3.9.2`\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nI can successfully compile a contract with a function that reads from the current state the contract address (i.e. I use `self`) and use the decorator `@pure`. You can check the function [`_compute_address_self`](https://github.com/pcaversaccio/snekmate/blob/main/src/utils/Create2Address.vy#L19) and change the decorator to `@pure` instead (`@view` is the correct decorator here IMHO). The compilation will not fail. In my understanding (tbf my homebase is Solidity) this should fail.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nPrevent state reading actions for `@pure` decorated functions.",
